{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":21083,"record_hash":"sha256:fbc01cbffa40631e00f3c96c7aabb078a5a41abf3f34810b861ab9a8b597ce6f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T20:34:00.967Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 9c6a91\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1065\nOutput:\n# GitMeta Data Model\n\n## Principles\n\n- Store durable agent sessions on the `project` target by default.\n- Use shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys for GitButler agentlog data.\n- Do not use `meta:local:*` for main session records.\n- Redact copied transcript strings before writing.\n- Keep branch, pull request, change, and commit links as future references to\n  durable project sessions, not owners of transcript data.\n- Do not write standard `agent:*` keys until there is an interoperability or\n  publication contract.\n- Do not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync in the POC.\n- Do not persist capture-run buckets. Each invocation merges transcript records\n  into the same durable session data.\n\n## Storage Shape\n\nSession index:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nDurable session prefix:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nSession-level keys:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:updated-at = <session update timestamp>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:sources = set<source-key>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:transcript = list<TranscriptRecord JSON>\n```\n\nSource-level keys:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:agent\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:provider\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:model\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n```\n\nDo not store full transcript paths, source file names, git branch names, or raw\nprovider session ids as session/source metadata.\n\n## Session And Source Keys\n\nProvider session ids are opaque and may contain private identifiers. Do not put\nthe raw provider session id in GitMeta keys or scalar values.\n\nFor this POC, derive `session-key` as `sha256-` plus the first 16 bytes of the\nSHA-256 digest, hex encoded:\n\n```text\nsha256-hex16(agent \n[TRUNCATED]\n transcript path bytes.\n\n## Transcript Records\n\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item\nis one redacted JSON transcript record with only per-record data:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n\t\"record_index\": 0,\n\t\"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T09:08:43.427Z\",\n\t\"event_kind\": \"response_item\",\n\t\"role\": \"assistant\",\n\t\"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n\t\"tool_name\": null,\n\t\"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSlim normalized fields support timeline browsing and handoff without reparsing\nevery provider-specific record:\n\n- `event_kind`: provider event type, with a nested event type when obvious\n- `role` and `content_text`: conversation body when extraction is obvious\n- `tool_name`: obvious tool activity\n- `source_record`: redacted provider record for provenance and future adapters\n\nOmit repeated session/source metadata from each transcript record. Also omit git\nbranch, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, and turn ids from\ntop-level record fields.\n\nRecord hashes and dedupe use the original trimmed JSONL bytes, not the redacted\ntranscript record.\n\n## Deduplication\n\nUse stable record hashes:\n\n```text\nsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n```\n\nTranscript append dedupe is rebuilt from the stored transcript list by reading\neach record's `record_hash`. Re-running capture against the same transcript is a\nno-op unless the transcript grew.\n\n## Future Association Model\n\nDo not attach transcript data directly to branches, commits, changes, or pull\nrequests in the POC. The project session is the durable object.\n\nLater, when GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nSee [Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md) for access patterns and product\nmotivation.\n\n## Publication\n\nThe POC writes shareable-ready keys but does not publish them. GitMeta\nserialization, push, fetch, and sync require a later privacy and product\ndecision.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T20:34:00.967Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}